Today marks the fifth anniversary of the deadly shooting at the Tree of Life Synagogue in Pittsburgh, the deadliest act of Antisemitism in US history. 11 people were killed and many more were wounded, including first responders. This remembrance comes shortly after the deadliest day for the Jewish people since the Holocaust, with Hamas attacking Israel on a sacred Jewish holiday. The rise of Antisemitism both abroad and at home has increased fear within the Jewish community. The Biden administration is taking steps to combat Antisemitism, including increasing security at Jewish centers, prioritizing hate crime prosecutions, passing gun safety laws, and implementing a national strategy to counter Antisemitism. The article emphasizes the importance of speaking out against bigotry and hate in all its forms and coming together as Americans to heal the nation.